  "title": "Cybersecurity Talent & Leadership Development Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job description</strong><br /><br /><strong>Data Management and Reporting</strong><br /><strong>- </strong>Maintain and update systems for tracking employee competencies, certifications, and progress in development programs<br />- Collect and compile data for program analysis, assisting the Senior Manager in the creation of reports and presentations for leadership\\<br />- Help to prepare data visualizations using tools like Tableau and Excel to illustrate program engagement and outcomes.</p><p><strong>Content and Communications</strong><br /><strong>- </strong>Assist in the development and curation of learning materials and resources for our cybersecurity professionals.<br />- Draft communications to promote engagement in our talent development initiatives, ensuring that employees are aware of available opportunities.<br />- Gather feedback from program participants to help identify areas for improvement.</p><p><strong>Stakeholder Engagement</strong><br /><strong>- </strong>Support the Senior Manager in engaging with stakeholders by preparing materials for meetings and presentations.<br />- Collaborate with HR and cybersecurity teams to ensure smooth program implementation.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br />- A Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field is preferred.<br />- A minimum of 3-5 years of experience in a talent development, learning and development, or HR coordination role.<br />- Strong organizational and coordination skills with a high degree of attention to detail.<br />- Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to interact effectively with employees at all levels.<br />- A proactive and collaborative approach to problem-solving.<br /></p><p><strong>Required Skills:</strong><br />-Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite, particularly Excel and PowerPoint.<br />- Experience with learning management systems (LMS) and data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau) is a plus.<br />- An interest in cybersecurity and a willingness to learn about the field is highly desirable.<br /></p><p>Working Days: Monday to Friday 8.30am-5.30pm<br />Location: Punggol/ Buona Vista/ Hybrid (Mixture)<br />Contract 1 year role (from immediate to 1 December 2026)<br /></p><p>EA License No: 96C4864<br />Reg. No.: R24121728 EUNICE WOO JING QI</p>",
